  "Highlights.20. Comments about Co-op management practices overall?": [
    "**Strong Positive Experiences with Direct Management:** Many employees express high satisfaction with their immediate managers, describing them as supportive, communicative, empathetic, and effective in problem-solving. These direct relationships are frequently cited as key to positive work experiences.",
    "**Significant Distrust and Criticism of Upper Management/HR:** A recurring theme is a strong distrust and negative experiences with upper management and the People & Culture (HR) department. Concerns include dismissiveness, defensiveness, lack of empathy, perceived favoritism, and inadequate handling of serious issues, leading to feelings of insecurity and a lack of accountability.",
    "**Inconsistencies in Accountability and Fairness:** There are consistent complaints about inconsistent application of corrective action, leniency towards underperforming or problematic employees, and a general lack of fairness, which negatively impacts morale and creates additional burdens for diligent staff."
