  "Highlights.27. Comments about workplace communications?": [
    "**Inter-Departmental and Inter-Location Communication Breakdown:** A predominant and strong negative theme is the severe lack of effective communication between different departments and especially between the two store locations (CWM and CDT). This leads to information falling through the cracks, last-minute needs, and a general feeling of working in a \"void.\"",
    "**Ineffective Feedback Mechanisms and Dismissed Staff Input:** Many employees feel their suggestions and concerns are not seriously considered or are outright dismissed, particularly in departments like Produce. Manager check-ins are often seen as ineffective, and there's a perceived lack of interest from management in hearing detailed reports or addressing recurring issues.",
    "**Positive Direct & Informal Communication, but Systemic Issues Persist:** While some employees highlight positive face-to-face interactions and the open atmosphere among staff, and appreciate specific communication tools like whiteboard posts or individual manager check-ins, these informal successes are overshadowed by systemic failures in formal communication channels and processes."
  ],
