      "comment": "I came in as a manager earning around $60k. Several staff members who report to me, and who have been here longer, are making the same amount. While I respect their experience, it's odd that there's no pay differentiation for added responsibility or leadership. The lack of merit-based raises also removes any real incentive to exceed expectations, since raises are standardized annually, regardless of performance. The job posting listed a range of $60 to $65k, and with my experience, which is more than sufficient for the role, I was surprised not to be offered the top end. It would also be helpful to know what the pay ceiling is for this position. Benefits are good and the HR team does care and want to be fair. Fair is hard, so I get it.",
