  "Highlights.34. Comments about compensation and benefits?": [
    "**Highly Valued Health Benefits & Perks:** The Co-op's fully covered health, dental, and vision insurance, along with the staff discount and Snack Shack, are consistently highlighted as exceptional and deeply appreciated benefits, making it a desirable employer.",
    "**Significant Dissatisfaction with Wages & Cost of Living:** A major point of concern is the inadequacy of wages to meet the high cost of living in Bozeman, leading to employees struggling financially, living paycheck-to-paycheck, and feeling underpaid relative to their efforts or similar roles elsewhere. This is exacerbated by disappointing annual raises that don't keep pace with inflation.",
    "**Demand for Merit-Based Raises and Fair Compensation Structure:** There is a strong, repeated call for implementing merit-based raises to incentivize high performance and differentiate pay for added responsibilities or leadership. The current system of standardized annual raises is seen as demotivating and unfair to diligent employees."
  ],
