  "Highlights.42. Comments about store/location operations?": [
    "**Critical Safety & Sanitation Concerns, Especially in Produce/Food Service:** There are very strong and detailed complaints about unsafe working conditions (crowded coolers, heavy lifting, parking lot safety) and severe sanitation issues, particularly in the produce department (mold, lack of cleaning regimen) and food service kitchen (broken sanitizer, poor night cleaning). These concerns are often reported as being ignored or dismissed until reaching a critical point.",
    "**Widespread Inter-Departmental Communication & Cooperation Failures:** Numerous comments highlight a \"huge lack\" of communication and teamwork between departments and locations, leading to inefficiencies, miscommunications, and a sense of animosity or alienation. Employees feel that information doesn't flow properly, and management often operates in silos, hindering overall operational effectiveness.",
    "**Inadequate Tools, Technology, and Resistance to Operational Changes:** Employees feel they lack the necessary tools and technology to perform their jobs optimally, citing outdated systems and unaddressed requests for improvements. There's also a perceived resistance from management to modify long-standing operational processes or consider new ideas, creating frustration and hindering progress."
  ],
