  "Highlights.51. Comments about department operations?": [
    "**Widespread Inconsistency in Standards and Accountability:** A dominant negative theme, particularly in the Produce department, is the perception of vastly different standards applied to employees, with some \"getting away with being extremely lazy\" while others are held to much higher expectations. This leads to frustration, feeling undervalued, and the diligent staff picking up the slack.",
    "**Recurring Issues with Communication & Management Responsiveness:** Employees frequently report that their concerns, suggestions for improvement, and issues like mold or improper product rotation are ignored, dismissed, or met with lukewarm \"nothing-responses\" from management, fostering a sense of not being heard or respected.",
    "**Overwhelm and Stress from Understaffing and Workload:** Many comments describe feeling \"overwhelmed\" and that the work is \"mentally and emotionally exhausting\" due to understaffing (e.g., in Front End and Support Staff, leading to predicted high turnover), leading to efficiency becoming \"a matter of survival\" rather than a well-managed process."
  ],
