  "Highlights.58. Comments about People & Culture practices?": [
    "**Widespread Distrust and Perception of P&C (HR) Bias:** A dominant negative theme is a strong and pervasive distrust of the People & Culture department, perceived as biased towards management, dismissing complaints, and defensive when feedback is given. Many employees feel P&C is ineffective, inconsistent in policy application, and not truly \"for the employees.\"",
    "**Failure to Address Discrimination and Inconsistent Support for Marginalized Employees:** Despite some positive comments about the Co-op's inclusivity ideals, there are severe criticisms regarding P&C's (and management's) failure to effectively address misgendering, transphobia, and other forms of discrimination or microaggressions, particularly from customers. This leads to doubts about the protection of marginalized staff.",
    "**Skepticism Towards Rebranding and Disconnect from Employee Realities:** Many employees view the \"People & Culture\" rebranding as superficial, a mere name change from HR, and feel the department is disconnected from the daily realities and economic struggles of the \"downstairs\" staff. There's a call for a stronger, more empathetic presence that genuinely makes employees feel safe."
  ],
