  "Highlights.67. Comments on training and development?": [
    "**Inconsistent and Inadequate Training Programs:** A significant concern is the chaotic, rushed, and often insufficient nature of training, especially for new employees or those without prior experience. Training is perceived as often failing to cover all job demands, leading to a lack of confidence and basic knowledge, and hindering long-term staff development.",
    "**Ineffective and Pressured Check-ins:** While some appreciate constructive check-ins, many employees, particularly long-term staff and cashiers, find the bi-annual check-ins to be pointless, too frequent, generalized, and even stressful, with a perceived pressure to create artificial goals rather than addressing real development needs or acknowledging existing good performance.",
    "**Managerial Misunderstanding of Roles and Unfair Expectations:** There are specific complaints about managers misunderstanding employee job descriptions, leading to uncomfortable situations where staff are asked to perform tasks outside their role or are given tone-deaf feedback that dismisses their struggles (e.g., being told to \"step up\" when overwhelmed by workload)."
  ],
